## ğŸ” Findings
- Each file format begins with a unique hexadecimal signature (magic number)  
- These signatures help identify file types even if extensions are changed  
- Example:
- JPG files typically start with `FF D8 FF`  
- PDF files start with `25 50 44 46`  
- Hex analysis allows detection of disguised or tampered files  

## ğŸ“š Lessons Learned
- Hexadecimal representation is the lowest-level view of digital data  
- File signatures are critical in forensic validation and recovery  
- Hex editors help uncover hidden data and file manipulation  
- This technique is essential for detecting anti-forensics techniques
